This paper deals with spatio-temporal data processing, which is a common topic in the database community (cs.DB). The paper also introduces a framework that uses machine learning techniques to predict updates to a trajectory database, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the scalability of the database, which is a topic in distributed systems (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper proposes a compression technique, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SP).
